description:
The Nashville sound (DVD)

(87 min.) :

Grand ole opry 

Summary: 	

Performances are interspersed among interviews with the stars, the fans and music industry people.

Contents: 	

Intro -- Earl Scruggs -- Porter Wagoner -- Dolly Parton -- Billy Monroe & His Blue Grass Boys -- Trying to make it -- Jeannie C. Riley -- Herbie Howell -- Fan clubs -- Loretta Lynn -- Recording session -- Tracy Nelson & Mother Earth -- "I got a contract!" -- Roy Acuff & The Smokey Mountain Boys -- Tex Ritter -- Lester Flatt -- The Stoney Mountain Cloggers & the Crook Bros. -- Jeannie C. Riley (part 2) -- Bob Lumar & Jimmie Riddle -- Charley Pride -- Johnny Cash & the Tennessee Three -- Performer credits -- Herbie Howell (part 2).
